-- Portugal's BES submitted plan for capital increase- regulator 
-- 
-- Wed May 14, 2014 11:56AM EDT
-- None



LISBON, May 14 (Reuters) - Banco Espirito Santo (BES) <BES.LS>, Portugal's second largest listed bank, has submitted a plan for a capital increase to the country's CMVM markets regulator, a spokeswoman at the regulator said on Wednesday.

"CMVM is analysing an operation for a capital increase by BES," the spokeswoman told Reuters without providing any further details.